	Condom army call    
	London May 16: Britain has launched a campaign warning its women soldiers to carry condoms after reports of a rise in pregnancies at its bases in Afghanistan. Advertisements in the Armys official magazine Soldier warned that on deployment, therell be 50 blokes to each woman and urged the female squad, medics and administrative staff to use a condom or face something you really dont want to hear.       
	Between January 2003 and February 2009, at least 102 servicewomen in Iraq had been sent home after it was found that they were pregnant, the Mail reported today.    
	Sex amp; sleep    
	 Washington: Its already known that levels of testosterone decline with age. But for the first time a new study has linked the decreasing levels of the male sex hormone to lack of sleep in middle-aged men. Researchers at the Department of Psychology of University of Montreal, Canada, found that testosterone levels begin to drop by one per cent annually when men reach 30.     
	Posh art    
	 London: Former Spice Girl Victoria Beckham and footballer husband David have secretly put together a modern art haul worth 30 million and are putting it up for display now. The entire collection, bought over eight years, is love themed. It includes paintings and sculptures by the likes of Damien Hirst and Bansky, reported the Mirror online.                                                                                                                                                      
